metadata:

hadiths[11]{hadithnumber,arabicnumber,text,reference_book,reference_hadith,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro,urdu,chapter_title_arabic}:
2780,1171.01,Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with both of them) reported that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to observe i'tikaf in the last ten days of Ramadan,14,1,,,,,,موسیٰ بن عقبہ نے نافع سے اور انھوں نے حضرت ابن عمر  رضی اللہ تعالیٰ عنہ  سے روایت کی کہ نبی اکرم  صل,2780,
2781,1171.02,"Abdullah b. Umar (Allah be pleased with both of them) reported that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to observe i'tikaf in the last ten days of Ramadan. Nafi' said:Abdullah (Allah be pleased with him) showed me the place in the mosque where the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to observe i'tikaf",14,2,,,,,,یونس بن یزید نے مجھے خبر دی کہ نافع نے انھیں حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ تعالیٰ عنہ  کے واسطے سے حد,2781,
2782,1172.01,A'isha (Allah be pleased with her) reported that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to observe i'tikaf in the last ten days of Ramadan,14,3,,,,,,عبدالرحمان بن قاسم نے اپنے والد سے ، انھوں نے حضرت عائشہ  رضی اللہ تعالیٰ عنہا   سے روایت کی ، انھوں,2782,
2783,1172.02,This hadith has been narrated by 'A'isha (Allah be pleased with her) through another chain of transmitters,14,4,,,,,,ہشام بن عروہ نے اپنے والد ( عروہ  )  سے ، انھوں نے حضرت عائشہ  رضی اللہ تعالیٰ عنہا   سے روایت کی ، ,2783,
2784,1172.03,A'isha (Allah be pleased with her) reported that the Messenger of Allah (may peace he upon him) used to observe i'tikif in the last ten days of Ramadan till Allah called him back (to his heavenly home). Then his wives observed i'tikaf after him,14,5,,,,,,زہری نے عروہ کے واسطے سے حضرت عائشہ  رضی اللہ تعالیٰ عنہا   سے روایت کی کہ نبی کریم  صلی اللہ علیہ و,2784,
2785,1173.01,"A'isha (Allah be pleased with her) reported that when the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) decided to observe i'tikaf, he prayed in the morning and then went to the place of his i'tikaf, and he commanded that a tent should be pitched for him, and it was pitched. He (once) decided to observe i'tikaf in the last ten days of Ramadan. Zainab (the wife of the Holy Prophet) commanded that a tent should be pitched for her. It was pitched accordingly. And some other wives of Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) commanded that tents should be pitched for them too. And they were pitched. When the Messenger of Allah (may peace he upon him) offered the morning prayer, he looked and found (so many) tents. Thereupon he said:What is this virtue that these (ladies) have decided to acquire? He commanded his tent to be struck and abandoned i'tikaf in the month of Ramadan and postponed it to the first ten days of Shawwal",14,6,,,,,,ابو معاویہ نے ہمیں یحییٰ بن سعید سے خبر دی ، انھوں نے عمرہ سے ، انھوں نے حضرت عائشہ  رضی اللہ تعالیٰ,2785,
2786,1173.02,"This hadith has been reported through another chain of transmitters, and there it is mentioned that. 'A'isha, Hafsa and Zainab (Allah be pleased with them) pitched the tents for i'tikaf",14,7,,,,,,سفیان بن عینیہ ، عمرو بن حارث ، سفیان ثوری ، اوزاعی ، اور محمد بن اسحاق سب نے یحییٰ بن سعید سے ، انھ,2786,
2787,1174,"A'isha (Allah be pleased with her) reported that when the last ten nights began Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) kept awake at night (for prayer and devotion), wakened his family, and prepared himself to observe prayer (with more vigour)",14,8,,,,,,"مسروق نے حضرت عائشہ سے روایت کی کہ ام المؤمنین عائشہ صدیقہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں  : کہ رسول اللہ صل",2787,
2788,1175,A'isha (Allah be pleased with her) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) used to exert himself in devotion during the last ten nights to a greater extent than at any other time,14,9,,,,,,"حسن بن عبیداللہ سے روایت ہے   ، کہا : میں نے ابراہیم نخعی سےسنا ، کہہ رہے تھے : میں نے اسود بن یزید ",2788,
2789,1176.01,"A'isha (Allah be pleased with her) reported:I never saw the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) fasting in the ten days of Dhu'I-Hijja",14,10,,,,,,ابو معاویہ نے اعمش سے ، انھوں نےابراہیم سے ، انھوں نے اسود سے ، انھوں نے حضرت عائشہ  رضی اللہ تعالیٰ,2789,
2790,1176.02,"A'isha (Allah be pleased with her) reported:The Apostle of Allah (ﷺ) did not observe fast in the ten days of Dhul-Hijja",14,11,,,,,,سفیان نے اعمش سے باقی ماندہ سابقہ سند کے ساتھ حضرت عائشہ  رضی اللہ تعالیٰ عنہا   سے روایت کی کہ اللہ,2790,
